\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 39. F. parviflora} Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot.}{\b  2}: 567 (1788) ({\i F. caespitosa} Loscos). Lobes of leaves very narrowly linear, channelled. Raceme 7(-10)- to 15(-22)-flowered, subsessile. Bracts as long as or longer than the fruiting pedicels. Sepals 0·5-0·7 × 0·5-0·7 mm, laciniate-dentate. Corolla white, occasionally flushed pink; lower petal spathulate with patent margin. Fruit 1·6-2·3 × 1·7-2·5 mm, subglobose, distinctly keeled and often subacute. 2n = 32. {\i W., S. & S.C. Europe, extending locally to C. Ukraine}. Be Bl Br Bu Co Cr Ga Ge Gr Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs(W) Sa Si Tu.
