\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. spicatus} (L.) Bernh.,{\i  Linnaea}{\b  8}: 471 (1833) ({\i Fumaria spicata} L.). More or less glaucous annual. Stems up to 30 cm, stout, branched, leafy. Ultimate leaf-segments 4-5 × 0·4-0·5 mm, mucronulate. Racemes 2·5-5 cm, subglobose to ovoid; bracts lanceolate to ovate, about twice as long as pedicels; pedicels recurved in fruit. Flowers 5-6 mm, whitish or yellowish, dark purple at apex of petals; sepals 1/6-1/3 as long as petals, entire or denticulate, caducous. Fruit ovate, flat or convex, obtuse, mucronate. 2n = 32.{\i  Cultivated ground. S.W. Europe, extending eastwards to S. Italy.} Bl Ga Hs It Lu Si.
\par

